1
00:00:51,479 --> 00:00:52,759
What a massive root system.

2
00:00:53,359 --> 00:00:54,280
Look at that moss.

3
00:00:55,359 --> 00:00:56,000
Kid,

4
00:00:56,479 --> 00:00:58,560
didn't you say you came back from abroad?

5
00:00:58,719 --> 00:01:00,159
Why do you act like you've never seen the world?

6
00:01:00,159 --> 00:01:01,240
Why are you messing with that stuff?

7
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:02,719
What's down here is what's worth studying.

8
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:20,159
Lao Lu,

9
00:01:20,519 --> 00:01:21,480
take a look at this.

10
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:23,159
What is this thing carrying the stone stele?

11
00:01:23,439 --> 00:01:24,599
Haven't we seen this thing before?

12
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:26,640
When have I ever seen this thing?

13
00:01:27,359 --> 00:01:29,120
In Tai'an, visiting the Dai Temple.

14
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:30,760
Right, right, right.

15
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,439
That's why you're Commander Chen.

16
00:01:32,439 --> 00:01:33,159
You have such a great memory.

17
00:01:33,599 --> 00:01:35,000
Back then, you even taught me how to pronounce its name.

18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,519
It was super hard to pronounce. What was it?

19
00:01:36,599 --> 00:01:38,920
Bei, bei, bei... Shi-bei?

20
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,079
Bixi.

21
00:01:41,159 --> 00:01:43,200
Right, I was just about to say it.

22
00:01:43,359 --> 00:01:44,159
Those are the words.

23
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:45,680
Look here.

24
00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:47,799
The beast's head is held high,

25
00:01:48,599 --> 00:01:49,480
its turtle tail is stretched out,

26
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:50,920
and its four claws grip the ground.

27
00:01:51,159 --> 00:01:54,879
The turtle shell on its back must be the cloud base.

28
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,640
This is Bixi, one of the dragon's nine sons.

29
00:02:00,879 --> 00:02:02,640
There's a plane on top of this tree,

30
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:04,680
a coffin in its trunk,

31
00:02:05,799 --> 00:02:07,640
and a stone stele pops up from underneath it.

32
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,080
This is getting more and more bizarre.

33
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:11,680
Yeah.

34
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:14,479
Tell me, such a massive stone stele,

35
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:16,879
how did they get it under the tree?

36
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,680
But what about the black smoke and thunderstorm just now?

37
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,719
Where did they come from?

38
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:22,080
The thunderstorm could be explained as a coincidence,

39
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,120
but I really don't know about the black smoke.

40
00:02:24,479 --> 00:02:26,280
The banyan tree's root system is so developed,

41
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:28,199
it must be at least a thousand years old.

42
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:32,240
The key is, how did it suddenly split open?

43
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,879
There's no interlocking mechanism here.

44
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:37,840
And how did this stone stele rise up?

45
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,039
What do the words on it say?

46
00:02:41,479 --> 00:02:42,680
This is Large Seal script, right?

47
00:02:42,759 --> 00:02:44,560
Lao Lu, hurry up and see what's written on it.

48
00:02:45,439 --> 00:02:46,319
Right, right, right.

49
00:02:46,719 --> 00:02:47,879
Take a look quickly.

50
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:50,159
Is there an inscription on it saying

51
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:53,680
which way leads straight to the old King of Dian's lair?

52
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,080
Come, come, help me up.

53
00:02:56,479 --> 00:02:57,319
I'll climb up and take a look.

54
00:02:57,319 --> 00:02:58,000
Coming.

55
00:02:58,439 --> 00:03:00,960
One, two, three. Alright!

56
00:03:08,879 --> 00:03:10,840
Fallen from grace in this life,

57
00:03:13,919 --> 00:03:15,599
losing the precious treasure early.

58
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,560
Taking the artifact into the depths,

59
00:03:22,159 --> 00:03:23,599
forever returning to the underworld.

60
00:03:23,879 --> 00:03:25,400
The beautiful melody suddenly stops,

61
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,319
following the royal carriage to Mount Tai.

62
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,120
Bow.

63
00:03:29,319 --> 00:03:30,199
I say, Uncle Lu,

64
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:31,800
let's stop reading.

65
00:03:32,319 --> 00:03:33,599
You read it really well,

66
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,840
but I... I just took a look.

67
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,199
It's not just me,

68
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,000
none of us understood it.

69
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,280
Can you translate it for us?

70
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,560
The general meaning is,

71
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:45,199
Qin Shi Huang established three commanderies.

72
00:03:45,199 --> 00:03:46,879
By the end of the Qin Dynasty,

73
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:47,879
during the Chu-Han Contention,

74
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:48,879
the world was in chaos.

75
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,759
The kings of these three commanderies

76
00:03:50,759 --> 00:03:51,639
each served their own masters,

77
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,840
and established their own kingdoms.

78
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,800
Later, when the Han Dynasty unified the world,

79
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:55,879
Emperor Wu of Han

80
00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:57,199
demanded from the King of Dian

81
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:59,639
this divine artifact, the Lingxiao Pearl.

82
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:03,680
The King of Dian fled deep into the mountains of western Dian

83
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:05,919
to kick the bucket.

84
00:04:06,599 --> 00:04:07,400
No, no,

85
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,439
to cultivate.

86
00:04:08,759 --> 00:04:09,800
It also says here

87
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:13,840
that the Lingxiao Pearl is a phoenix transformed by the Earth Mother.

88
00:04:14,439 --> 00:04:15,439
They believed that

89
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:18,519
by using this, one could be reborn

90
00:04:18,519 --> 00:04:19,800
and achieve immortality.

91
00:04:20,319 --> 00:04:21,560
Old Chen, look at this.

92
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:23,360
A rare occurrence in a thousand years,

93
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,920
the body perishes with the Dao.

94
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:27,439
Within the water dragon's halo,

95
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,560
one achieves immortality through Shijie.

96
00:04:32,319 --> 00:04:34,240
He was thinking about achieving immortality through Shijie.

97
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,160
Shijie?

98
00:04:36,519 --> 00:04:38,360
Shijie? Where?

99
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,399
Is she pretty?

100
00:04:41,759 --> 00:04:42,839
Shi as in corpse.

101
00:04:43,519 --> 00:04:46,040
You mean the corpse rotting and decomposing?

102
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,120
The Shijie we're talking about

103
00:04:48,519 --> 00:04:50,120
is a Taoist magical art,

104
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,879
a method of ascending to immortality.

105
00:04:52,079 --> 00:04:53,680
It means that a person who has attained the Dao

106
00:04:53,879 --> 00:04:55,959
leaves their corpse in the mortal world after death,

107
00:04:55,959 --> 00:04:57,800
while their true self transforms into an immortal.

108
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:00,439
There's a recent novel about this.

109
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,639
Go read it yourself.

110
00:05:01,839 --> 00:05:02,600
Lao Chen.

111
00:05:02,639 --> 00:05:04,480
You're making it too hard for the kid.

112
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:05,800
I reckon he...

113
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,279
...can barely read a few Chinese characters.

114
00:05:07,279 --> 00:05:08,480
Let alone read a novel.

115
00:05:09,959 --> 00:05:12,480
You can read all these ancient characters?

116
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:15,639
Of course.

117
00:05:15,639 --> 00:05:16,959
This is nothing.

118
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,920
Our Lao Lu is very capable.

119
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,199
I've always felt that ancient Chinese characters...

120
00:05:22,199 --> 00:05:23,480
...have a mysterious beauty to them.

121
00:05:23,639 --> 00:05:24,920
I was just worrying about not finding a teacher.

122
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:28,680
Teacher Lu, can I call you that?

123
00:05:29,199 --> 00:05:30,959
A strong thirst for knowledge is a good thing.

124
00:05:30,959 --> 00:05:32,879
Feel free to ask if there's anything you don't understand.

125
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:34,879
About that corpse liberation thing we just talked about...

126
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,079
Do you understand it now?

127
00:05:36,879 --> 00:05:38,399
I think I get the gist of it.

128
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:40,879
Is it like a cicada...

129
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,240
...shedding its skin?

130
00:05:43,079 --> 00:05:43,800
Exactly.

131
00:05:44,319 --> 00:05:45,360
Let me teach you an idiom.

132
00:05:45,639 --> 00:05:47,279
The golden cicada sheds its shell.

133
00:05:48,439 --> 00:05:49,600
The golden cicada sheds its shell.

134
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,959
If the Dian King's tomb is really as it says here...

135
00:05:52,959 --> 00:05:54,720
...the jade coffin in the tree should be...

136
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,879
...one of the star positions around the main tomb.

137
00:05:57,560 --> 00:06:00,120
Then we've ruined the feng shui of the main tomb.

138
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,839
Isn't that pretty serious?

139
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:08,079
Or else why did we almost get struck by lightning?

140
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:09,639
It shouldn't be that serious.

141
00:06:10,279 --> 00:06:11,399
We didn't really disturb it.

142
00:06:12,199 --> 00:06:13,480
According to what's written here...

143
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,079
...this Dian King...

144
00:06:15,079 --> 00:06:17,959
...probably advocated witchcraft and sorcery.

145
00:06:18,319 --> 00:06:19,879
The important ministers around him...

146
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,560
...were probably feng shui masters and the like.

147
00:06:22,959 --> 00:06:24,560
The owner of this satellite tomb...

148
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:28,319
...has probably already achieved immortality and left.

149
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,399
That's why it's empty.

150
00:06:30,839 --> 00:06:32,480
Teacher Lu, I have a question.

151
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:33,680
Go ahead.

152
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,319
When life ends...

153
00:06:35,319 --> 00:06:36,480
...metabolism stops...

154
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,800
...and all cells die.

155
00:06:38,079 --> 00:06:39,399
Then bacteria invade...

156
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:42,360
...and the body decomposes into mold, monosaccharides...

157
00:06:42,399 --> 00:06:44,360
...water, amino acids, and lipids.

158
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,519
This doesn't seem to have anything to do...

159
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,920
...with the immortality you mentioned.

160
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,319
Well, what you're talking about...

161
00:06:54,399 --> 00:06:56,040
...is probably the Western...

162
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,040
...theoretical system of what happens after death.

163
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,399
What we are discussing now is...

164
00:06:59,399 --> 00:07:00,720
...the ancient Chinese...

165
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,639
...theoretical system of what happens after death.

166
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:04,879
As the old saying goes...

167
00:07:04,879 --> 00:07:06,360
Know yourself and your enemy, and you will never be defeated.

168
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:07,560
If we don't understand this nonsense...

169
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,120
...how can we criticize it?

170
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:09,879
Right?

171
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:15,399
Lao Lu.

172
00:07:15,639 --> 00:07:17,040
Is there any record on this...

173
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,959
...about the location of the Dian King's tomb?

174
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:21,000
It really doesn't say.

175
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:22,160
All right.

176
00:07:22,399 --> 00:07:23,639
Looks like there are no shortcuts.

177
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,319
Let's stick to the original plan...

178
00:07:25,319 --> 00:07:27,480
...and head up along the Shepazi River.

179
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,199
Let's go.

180
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,319
Wait, don't just leave like this.

181
00:07:32,439 --> 00:07:34,399
It's rare to see such a good thing.

182
00:07:34,399 --> 00:07:36,680
I have to make a rubbing of it.

183
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:39,120
Teacher Lu, let me help you.

184
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:40,800
Okay, okay, bring me my bag.

185
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:41,600
Okay, I'll get the bag.

186
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,480
Lao Chen.

187
00:08:25,319 --> 00:08:26,959
Why is the fog getting thicker?

188
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:29,680
Big Guy, this is a river valley.

189
00:08:30,079 --> 00:08:32,039
It's quite humid and low-lying.

190
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:33,679
This fog...

191
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,440
...probably won't clear up anytime soon.

192
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,080
Why do I feel like...

193
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,360
...there's something wrong with the air?

194
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:45,759
Yeah, it doesn't feel very comfortable.

195
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:47,399
I don't feel well either.

196
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,320
Could it be miasma?

197
00:08:55,279 --> 00:08:55,960
Lao Lu!

198
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:57,240
Lao Lu!

199
00:08:57,679 --> 00:08:58,480
Are you okay?

200
00:08:58,679 --> 00:08:59,399
Hurry!

201
00:08:59,519 --> 00:09:00,320
Get the towels!

202
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:02,240
Wet them and cover your nose and mouth!

203
00:09:04,879 --> 00:09:05,240
Dawei!

204
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:06,120
Buddy, take this...

205
00:09:21,799 --> 00:09:22,600
Hey, Old Chen.

206
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,440
Let's just push hard

207
00:09:24,799 --> 00:09:26,000
and rush out of here.

208
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,080
We don't know how far this miasma spreads.

209
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,240
If we rush out now,

210
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,600
who knows if we'll make it out.

211
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,440
Then what do we do?

212
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:32,960
Should we head back?

213
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,000
When you're moving,

214
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,360
your blood circulation speeds up,

215
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,600
and you'll inhale more poison gas.

216
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,399
We can't go forward or backward.

217
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:44,240
We can't just wait here to die!

218
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:48,080
Wait.

219
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:50,759
Old Chen,

220
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,159
we've seen it all.

221
00:09:53,639 --> 00:09:54,840
Are we really just waiting to die?

222
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,440
It can't be that bad, right?

223
00:09:56,559 --> 00:09:57,360
Stop talking.

224
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:58,840
Don't move around.

225
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,840
Listen to me if you want to live.

226
00:10:18,279 --> 00:10:20,840
I mean, what's our plan now?

227
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:22,960
If we're really waiting to die,

228
00:10:23,399 --> 00:10:25,679
can I eat all the rations in my bag?

229
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,480
I don't want to die on an empty stomach.

230
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,480
Just stay where you are.

231
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,039
Stop talking so much.

232
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:34,399
If I could sit still,

233
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,159
I wouldn't be doing this.

234
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,080
Everyone, keep your mouths shut.

235
00:10:40,759 --> 00:10:41,960
Hold on a little longer.

236
00:10:59,159 --> 00:10:59,879
It's here.

237
00:11:00,919 --> 00:11:01,960
Finally here.

238
00:11:02,679 --> 00:11:03,480
It's here.

239
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,279
This miasma will dissipate when it meets water.

240
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,480
Lao Chen.

241
00:11:08,279 --> 00:11:10,879
Let's take this chance to rush out.

242
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,039
But we don't know what's ahead.

243
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:15,440
What if the rain stops and the miasma rises again?

244
00:11:16,279 --> 00:11:18,759
Why don't you have any spirit of adventure?

245
00:11:18,759 --> 00:11:19,720
Hurry up, let's go!

246
00:11:19,879 --> 00:11:21,879
How did your parents teach you?

247
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,120
Lao Chen.

248
00:11:30,279 --> 00:11:31,879
Are you the Monkey King in disguise?

249
00:11:31,879 --> 00:11:33,279
Or the reincarnation of the God of Thunder?

250
00:11:33,279 --> 00:11:34,679
You control the rain.

251
00:11:34,679 --> 00:11:35,679
The fire is completely put out.

252
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:37,279
Big Guy's clothes aren't even dry yet.

253
00:11:37,679 --> 00:11:39,200
But I still have to praise you.

254
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:40,960
If it weren't for your skills,

255
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,879
we would've been done for today.

256
00:11:42,879 --> 00:11:45,080
I know, this is called convectional rain.

257
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,480
In low-latitude tropical regions,

258
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:49,360
it rains often, usually in the afternoon.

259
00:11:49,679 --> 00:11:51,159
As the saying goes,

260
00:11:51,279 --> 00:11:53,279
look southeast in the morning, northwest in the evening.

261
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,600
Before entering the river valley,

262
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,679
I noticed altocumulus clouds to the southeast.

263
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,399
Plus the insects flying low,

264
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,200
I figured it would definitely rain around noon.

265
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:02,480
Impressive.

266
00:12:03,279 --> 00:12:04,960
Good thing we ran into this heavy rain.

267
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:07,080
Otherwise, we'd be trapped to death inside.

268
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,559
The rain is great.

269
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,039
It came at just the right time.

270
00:12:10,679 --> 00:12:14,559
Brother, did you say this is called miasma?

271
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:15,720
Yes.

272
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:18,240
It refers to the forests in the south and southwest,

273
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:20,559
a disease-causing gas from hot and humid evaporation.

274
00:12:20,879 --> 00:12:21,879
I still remember,

275
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:24,480
the Book of the Later Han's Southern Barbarians chapter,

276
